cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically semantic object segmentation in videos. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a semi-supervised approach that involves adapting a CNN image recognition model to the target domain, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with video data, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well.
